# Deploy-size trimming for Vercel.
#
# The threejs-player-and-grass race models ship as Unity FBX kits + TGA
# textures + per-state Mixamo FBX clips. Those total ~280 MB across 178
# files — way above Vercel's static deploy size budget. They live on
# objects.grudge-studio.com instead; GrudgeModelsSDK resolves every
# manifest `model` / `clipFiles` path against that origin.
#
# api/v1/race-models.json (the ~6 KB manifest) is NOT ignored — the SDK
# still fetches it from the same origin as the app.

# Entire demo app lives under /api/ so Vercel would bundle each .js as a
# serverless function (vite.config alone was 313 MB). Models are on CDN;
# only api/v1/race-models.json is served from this deploy.
api/threejs-player-and-grass/**

# Node + Vite build artefacts — never needed in the Vercel deploy.
**/node_modules/**
**/node_modules
**/dist-build/**
**/dist-build
**/.vite/**
**/.vite
